'''rlm_unix''' is the FreeRADIUS module that allows authentication/authorization via the Unix-style passwd/shadow/group files.

See also:
* [http://freeradius.org/radiusd/man/rlm_unix.html rlm_unix(5) manual]
* [[rlm_passwd]]

{{Default in the server source|src/modules/rlm_unix/}}

==Configuration==

{{Default in the server source|raddb/modules/unix}}

<pre>
	# Unix /etc/passwd style authentication
	#
	unix {
		#  As of 1.1.0, the Unix module no longer reads,
		#  or caches /etc/passwd, /etc/shadow, or /etc/group.
		#  If you wish to cache those files, see the passwd
		#  module, above.
		#

		#
		#  The location of the "wtmp" file.
		#  This should be moved to it's own module soon.
		#
		#  The only use for 'radlast'.  If you don't use
		#  'radlast', then you can comment out this item.
		#
		radwtmp = ${logdir}/radwtmp
	}
</pre>